<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="394" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2620: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-11T22:00:00+00:00">November 11, 1931—10
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 11—5:22
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>724. Your 530, November 9, 4 p.m., and my 721, November 11, noon.<note n="8" xml:id="d394fn8">Latter not printed.</note></p>
                        <p>This afternoon in talking with Briand I carefully gave him the substance
                            of your 530. He said he would endeavor to have proposed at next week’s
                            conference the plan which is described in paragraph (2) of your
                            telegram.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>